verses.text: The preparations of the heart in man , and the answer of the tongue , \add is\add* from the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*.\f + \fr 16.1 \ft preparations: or, disposings\f*
All the ways of a man \add are\add* clean in his own eyes ; but the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* weigheth the spirits.
Commit thy works unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, and thy thoughts shall be established.\f + \fr 16.3 \ft Commit: Heb. Roll\f*
The \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* hath made all \add things\add* for himself : yea, even the wicked for the day of evil.

Every one \add that is\add* proud in heart \add is\add* an abomination to the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*: \add though\add* hand \add join\add* in hand , he shall not be unpunished.\f + \fr 16.5 \ft unpunished: Heb. held innocent\f*
By mercy and truth iniquity is purged : and by the fear of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* \add men\add* depart from evil.
When a man’s ways please the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, he maketh even his enemies to be at peace with him.
Better \add is\add* a little with righteousness than great revenues without right.
A man’s heart deviseth his way : but the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* directeth his steps.
A divine sentence \add is\add* in the lips of the king : his mouth transgresseth not in judgment.\f + \fr 16.10 \ft A divine…: Heb. Divination\f*
A just weight and balance \add are\add* the \nd \+w LORD’s|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*: all the weights of the bag \add are\add* his work.\f + \fr 16.11 \ft the weights: Heb. the stones\f*
\add It is\add* an abomination to kings to commit wickedness : for the throne is established by righteousness.
Righteous lips \add are\add* the delight of kings ; and they love him that speaketh right. \p
The wrath of a king \add is as\add* messengers of death : but a wise man will pacify it.
In the light of the king’s countenance \add is\add* life ; and his favour \add is\add* as a cloud of the latter rain.
How much better \add is it\add* to get wisdom than gold ! and to get understanding rather to be chosen than silver !
The highway of the upright \add is\add* to depart from evil : he that keepeth his way preserveth his soul.
Pride \add goeth\add* before destruction , and an haughty spirit before a fall.
Better \add it is to be\add* of an humble spirit with the lowly , than to divide the spoil with the proud.
He that handleth a matter wisely shall find good : and whoso trusteth in the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, happy \add is\add* he.\f + \fr 16.20 \ft handleth…: or, understandeth a matter\f*
The wise in heart shall be called prudent : and the sweetness of the lips increaseth learning.
Understanding \add is\add* a wellspring of life unto him that hath it: but the instruction of fools \add is\add* folly.
The heart of the wise teacheth his mouth , and addeth learning to his lips.\f + \fr 16.23 \ft teacheth: Heb. maketh wise\f*
Pleasant words \add are as\add* an honeycomb , sweet to the soul , and health to the bones.
There is a way that seemeth right unto a man , but the end thereof \add are\add* the ways of death.
He that laboureth laboureth for himself; for his mouth craveth it of him.\f + \fr 16.26 \ft He…: Heb. The soul of him that\f*\f + \fr 16.26 \ft craveth…: Heb. boweth unto him\f* \p
An ungodly man diggeth up evil : and in his lips \add there is\add* as a burning fire.\f + \fr 16.27 \ft An…: Heb. A man of Belial\f*
A froward man soweth strife : and a whisperer separateth chief friends.\f + \fr 16.28 \ft soweth: Heb. sendeth forth\f* \p
A violent man enticeth his neighbour , and leadeth him into the way \add that is\add* not good.
He shutteth his eyes to devise froward things : moving his lips he bringeth evil to pass.
The hoary head \add is\add* a crown of glory , \add if\add* it be found in the way of righteousness.
\add He that is\add* slow to anger \add is\add* better than the mighty ; and he that ruleth his spirit than he that taketh a city.
The lot is cast into the lap ; but the whole disposing thereof \add is\add* of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*.
